$ add-apt-repository

`add-apt-repository` is a → development/languages/Python script that adds or removes an (external) → Linux/APT#apt-repositories[APT repository] from `→ Linux/fhs/etc/apt/sources_list` or `/etc/apt/sources.list.d`.

{ Examples

code {
apt-add-repository 'deb http://myserver/path/to/repo stable myrepo'
apt-add-repository 'http://myserver/path/to/repo myrepo'
apt-add-repository 'https://packages.medibuntu.org free non-free'
apt-add-repository http://extras.ubuntu.com/ubuntu
apt-add-repository ppa:user/repository
apt-add-repository ppa:user/distro/repository
apt-add-repository multiverse
code }

}

{ add-apt-repository: command not found

   Error message thrown:
code {
$ sudo add-apt-repository ppa:git-core/ppa -y
sudo: add-apt-repository: command not found
code }

   Try to fix it:
code {
$ sudo apt install software-properties-common
code }

   C'mon…
code {
$ sudo add-apt-repository ppa:git-core/ppa -y
  …
FileNotFoundError: [Errno 2] No such file or directory: 'gpg': 'gpg'
code }

   Try again
code {
$ sudo apt-get install gpg
code }

  Finally:
code {
$ sudo add-apt-repository ppa:git-core/ppa -y
code }

}
